<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLE WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Boycott Against Lang Beefs Up: More radio stations in the farm states of 
Minnesota, Nebraska and Iowa are joining the boycott of Grammy-winning singer 
k.d. lang because of her appearance in a "Meat Stinks" advertising campaign. 
</P>
<P>
Radio station KRVN in Lexington, Neb., had previously banned the singer because 
of the commercials. Patrick John, program director of KSUM-AM in Fairmont, 
Minn., said that his station won't play lang's music until she disavows People 
for the Ethical Treatment of Animals, which put together the campaign. KSRB-AM 
in Sioux Falls, S.D., tried a different approach -- it gave away filet mignon 
to callers each time it played one of lang's songs Tuesday. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
