<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FIREWORKS FEARS FORCE MULHOLLAND CLOSURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unpaved portion of Mulholland Drive that in the past has drawn hundreds of 
fireworks spectators was closed from 6 p.m. to midnight Wednesday because of 
fears that tinder-dry brush might catch fire. 
</P>
<P>
Closure of the five-mile dirt stretch between Encino Hills Drive and Trinidad 
Road was the first of its kind on Mulholland Drive, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
"Kids go up there in four-wheel-drives, and sometimes they get a little bit 
carried away," Los Angeles Fire Department Battalion Chief John Adams said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
