<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SPRING VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man whose nude body was found floating face down in Sweetwater Reservoir in 
Spring Valley was identified Wednesday as a 29-year-old San Diegan, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The body, identified as that of Johnny Smith by the San Diego County medical 
examiner's office, was spotted shortly after 7:30 p.m. Tuesday by a man who was 
fishing near a house that backs up to the waterline in the 9500 block of San 
Carlos Street, according to a Sheriff's Department spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
An autopsy determined that Smith drowned, but police said Wednesday that it was 
not known how Smith came to be in the water or why he was nude. The 
investigation into the incident is continuing, police said. 
</P>
