SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: NATIONAL CITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police are investigating the homicide of a man who was shot dead in a city 
apartment complex early Wednesday, apparently during an attempted robbery. 
</P>
<P>
The identity of the victim, who was described as a Latino male in his early 
20s, remained unknown. 
</P>
<P>
His body was found on the second-floor balcony of an apartment in the 1700 
block of McKinley Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the slaying occurred at about 8 a.m., when two men attempted to rob 
another man in the apartment complex. Someone fired a shotgun blast, police 
said, hitting the victim. Several suspects immediately fled the area, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
It was unclear whether the shotgun was wielded by the suspected thieves, an 
intended victim or a third party, according to investigators. 
