<P>
PAMPHLET CALLS FOR ATTACKS ON ARABS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pamphlet distributed among Jewish settlers urges them to shoot Palestinians 
and gives detailed instructions on how to obtain guns and avoid capture, 
according to Israeli media reports. The anonymous pamphlet advises settlers to 
gather explosives from the army, masquerade as soldiers during attacks and 
leave behind misleading evidence. It says the settlers in the occupied West 
Bank and Gaza Strip should respond to stoning attacks on their cars with 
gunfire and should try to "hit and cause much damage." 
</P>
