WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
IRAN; 
</P>
<P>
RAFSANJANI LOWERS QUAKE DEATH TOLL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Hashemi Rafsanjani toured quake-ravaged northwest Iran and said that 
the death toll from the June 21 temblor was less than 34,000, lower than first 
feared. "The figures were somewhat exaggerated in the villages," Iran's leader 
told Tehran Radio. His estimate contradicted one earlier in the day by Foreign 
Minister Ali Akbar Velayati, who told the U.N. Economic and Social Council in 
Geneva that 50,000 people were thought to have died. 
</P>
