<P>
1,300 ETHIOPIAN TROOPS SLAIN, REBELS REPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NAIROBI, Kenya 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rebels fighting for an independent Eritrea said they killed 1,300 Ethiopian 
government troops last weekend when they repulsed an army attack on the front 
line east of the Eritrean provincial capital, Asmara. 
</P>
<P>
The clandestine radio of the Eritrean People's Liberation Front said Tuesday 
night that the clash occurred when Ethiopian troops attacked rebel positions on 
the Adi Rosso front, about 20 miles east of Asmara. 
</P>
