<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRANCE TESTS A-BOMB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
France exploded a 35-kiloton nuclear bomb at its underground Pacific test site 
Wednesday, the Defense Ministry announced. The explosion was the second in just 
over two weeks and the fourth since President Francois Mitterrand pledged to be 
more open about the test program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
