<HEADLINE>
<P>
'DEAL' RETURNS -- AT 3:30 A.M. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Let's Make a Deal," one of the most popular game shows in television history, 
is returning to the airwaves Monday with new episodes. 
</P>
<P>
But aside from insomniacs and people who remember to set their VCRs, few 
Southern Californians will be able to see the show. 
</P>
<P>
That's because KNBC Channel 4 has scheduled "Let's Make a Deal" for weekdays at 
3:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Most NBC affiliates will air the program at 10 a.m., but KNBC carries "House 
Party" at that time. 
</P>
<P>
"We have a financial commitment to 'House Party' through September. When that 
commitment expires, KNBC will move 'Let's Make a Deal' to the daytime lineup," 
KNBC spokeswoman Regina Miyamoto said. STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TELEVISION PROGRAMS; GAME SHOWS; LETS MAKE A DEAL (TELEVISION PROGRAM); KNBC 
(TELEVISION STATION) 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
