<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: WEST HOLLYWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
$31.7-MILLION BUDGET OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council gave final approval to a $31.7-million operating budget for 
the fiscal year that began July 1. 
</P>
<P>
The budget includes about $650,000 in cuts that were made to make room for an 
expected $1.5-million drop in state funding next year. Hardest hit by the 
city's budget ax was the Public Works Department, which was eliminated to save 
more than $100,000. The City Council plans to trim an additional $750,000 from 
the 1991-92 budget. 
</P>
</TEXT>
