<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: CERRITOS; 
</P>
<P>
$74.6-MILLION BUDGET IS UP $8.6 MILLION OVER LAST YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The new fiscal budget in Cerritos is $8.6 million higher than last year's. 
Nevertheless, the city's approximately $20-million surplus is still intact and, 
overall, spending is still on a downward trend. 
</P>
<P>
This year's budget totals $74.6 million, in contrast to last year's $66 
million. The Redevelopment Agency's share this year is $42.2 million, compared 
to $35.8 million last year. 
</P>
<P>
In 1988-89, however, the city budget was about $90 million because the 
Redevelopment Agency was knee-deep in capital projects. Most of those are now 
complete. The biggest exception is the Community Arts Center, which is expected 
to cost $46.4 million by the time it is completed next year in the Cerritos 
Towne Center. 
</P>
<P>
When the council first authorized construction of the arts center three years 
ago, cost estimates were around $18 million. Since then, however, extensive 
architectural revisions have been made in order to allow the center to be used 
by community groups for meetings and other events. 
</P>
</TEXT>
