<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SOUTH EL MONTE; 
</P>
<P>
RULES FOR WASTE FACILITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council adopted an ordinance last week requiring all zoning, 
subdivision and land-use permits for hazardous-waste facilities to meet Los 
Angeles County specifications. 
</P>
<P>
Last November, the state Department of Health Services approved the county's 
new plan on hazardous-waste management. There are no hazardous-waste facilities 
operating in South El Monte, nor are any applying. City officials said the 
ordinance is a precaution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
