<P>
OFFICIALS' SALARIES CUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council last week cut the annual salaries of the assistant city 
manager and the administrative assistant to the city manager by $24,356 and 
$11,400 respectively. 
</P>
<P>
The two positions are vacant. 
</P>
<P>
During the 1990-91 fiscal year, the assistant city manager will earn $64,596, 
and the administrative assistant will earn $34,200. Meanwhile, City Manager 
Mark Lewis' salary will increase from $87,820 to $93,708. 
</P>
</TEXT>
