<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: WALNUT; 
</P>
<P>
ACTION ON MEADOWPASS ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One of the city's last incomplete main thoroughfares moved a step closer to 
completion last week. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council tentatively approved a housing subdivision plan that includes 
right-of-way for an unfinished link of Meadowpass Road just south of Amar Road. 
</P>
<P>
But the council effectively put the plan on hold by delaying a vote on the 
developer's request to put two of the proposed eight houses on lots that do not 
meet minimum size requirements. 
</P>
<P>
The recommendation from the Planning Commission was to deny the appeal, citing 
no extraordinary circumstances. The council voted to rehear the zoning issue at 
its Aug. 8 meeting. 
</P>
<P>
City planning officials say the completion of Meadowpass Road would alleviate 
traffic congestion along Pierre Road and Walnut Canyon Drive. But some 
residents say the reverse would be true, with more motorists gaining access to 
already-congested thoroughfares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
