WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICAS; 
</P>
<P>
PARK SERVICE EVENTS LISTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
National Park Service officials have announced a three-month schedule of 
outdoor events in and near the Santa Monica Mountains. 
</P>
<P>
Rangers from national and state park services, docents and volunteers will be 
leading a variety of nature walks, talks, and hikes through September, a park 
service spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The booklet "Summer in the Santa Monica Mountains and Seashore -- 1990," 
provides a complete listing of events. It is available free. To obtain a copy, 
call (818) 597-9192, or write to Calendar, Santa Monica Mountains National 
Recreation Area, 30401 Agoura Road, Suite 100, Agoura Hills, Calif. 91301. 
</P>
</TEXT>
