<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
REWARDS FOR SAVING WATER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Water users who reduce their consumption by 15% or more this summer will be 
rewarded with prizes of drought-tolerant seeds and plants and ultra-low volume 
toilets. 
</P>
<P>
The rewards are part of the Water Savers Awards Program to be conducted this 
month through September by the city's Water and Power Department. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, a group of water customers will be selected every two weeks, and 
their water usage compared with the same billing period in 1989. The two 
customers saving the most water during each two-week period will receive free 
toilets. 
</P>
<P>
Information on the water-saver program and on how to conserve can be obtained 
by calling (818) 584-WATER. 
</P>
</TEXT>
