<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: IRWINDALE; 
</P>
<P>
CITY MANAGER RESIGNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City Manager Charles R. Martin, 66, resigned last Thursday night after nearly 
17 years on the job. 
</P>
<P>
Alfred F. Herrera, Martin's longtime assistant, was named his permanent 
replacement. Herrera, 55, has served as acting city manager, including most of 
the last year while Martin recuperated from an illness. 
</P>
<P>
Martin will remain Irwindale city attorney and city clerk. On submitting his 
resignation to Irwindale Mayor Richard Chico, Martin said of his 
accomplishments as city manager: "Irwindale is on the map and has plenty of 
money." 
</P>
</TEXT>
