<HEADLINE>
<P>
PICK OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A re-creation of famous events in American history, sculpted from 380,000 
pounds of sand, is at the center court of Santa Anita Fashion Park through 
September. 
</P>
<P>
The sand sculptures include a 20-foot-tall replica of the Statue of Liberty, 
and life-size figures of Thomas Edison holding a light bulb and Alexander 
Graham Bell making the first telephone call. 
</P>
<P>
Abraham Lincoln is posed at a podium reading the Gettysburg Address. 
</P>
<P>
Events to be held in conjunction with the display include a program by the 
Talent Towners, ages 8 to 18, who will sing and dance at 1 p.m. Saturday. From 
noon to 2 p.m. July 14, 20 children from the Foothill Academy of Gymnastics 
will perform routines on mats and the balance beam. 
</P>
<P>
Fashion Park, at 400 S. Baldwin Ave., Arcadia, is open from 10 a.m. to 9 p.m. 
weekdays, 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Saturdays and 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. Sundays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, PICK OF THE WEEK: A re-creation of famous events in American history, 
sculpted from 380,000 pounds of sand, is at the center court of Santa Anita 
Fashion Park in Arcadia through September. KIRK McKOY / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
