<P>
HACKMAN AVOIDS HEART ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Gene Hackman narrowly avoided a heart attack when he checked into a 
Portland, Ore., hospital complaining of chest pain, his doctor said today. 
</P>
<P>
"We think we got him just in the nick of time," Dr. Herbert Semler said at a 
news conference after he treated the actor for partial blockage of a coronary 
blood vessel. 
</P>
<P>
Hackman, 60, was vacationing on the Oregon coast when he began suffering the 
pain. He was admitted Tuesday to St. Vincent Hospital &amp; Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
Semler said Hackman suffered from a narrowing of an artery leading to the 
heart. The doctor said he inserted a balloon catheter into the artery. 
</P>
<P>
Semler said he is recommending an exercise and diet plan for Hackman, who lives 
in Beverly Hills. 
</P>
