<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
BOXER PRYOR SETS N.Y. EYE EXAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aaron Pryor will have an eye examination by a New York Athletic Commission 
doctor Friday morning to determine if he can resume fighting in the state. 
</P>
<P>
Dr. Vincent Giovinazzi will check the progress of Pryor's recovery from 
January, 1989, surgery to remove cataracts and repair a detached retina in his 
left eye. 
</P>
<P>
After the surgery, the former junior welterweight champion was suspended from 
fighting in New York, Nevada, New Jersey and California. 
</P>
<P>
He has since received clearance to fight in the Manitoba province of Canada, 
having passed an eye exam there. 
</P>
<P>
Friday's examination, originally scheduled earlier in the week, was postponed 
at the convenience of the doctor. 
</P>
