<HEADLINE>
<P>
JULIE KRONE HEADING BACK TO THE SADDLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The nation's leading female jockey, Julie Krone, returns to the saddle Saturday 
at Monmouth Park, Oceanport, N.J. Krone will simply exercise a few horses for 
trainer John Forbes, but has indicated she plans to return to race riding by 
the end of the month. Krone underwent bone grafts and prolonged rehabilitation 
therapy after a Nov. 24 spill at the Meadowlands in New Jersey, where she 
sustained severe arm injuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
